{{Otheruses|subject=[[同性戀者|同性戀者]]的代稱|other=這一稱呼的其它用法|同志}}
'''同志'''是[[中文|中文]]語境中對[[同性戀者|同性戀者]]的代稱之一，廣義上也可以指代[[LGBT|LGBT]]（即[[女同性戀|女同性戀]]、[[男同性戀|男同性戀]]、[[雙性戀|雙性戀]]、[[跨性別|跨性別]]）等性少數群體。「同志」一詞的這一用法於20世紀80年代末在[[香港|香港]]興起，並逐漸流傳到了[[台灣|台灣]]和[[中國大陸|中國大陸]]等華語地區。時至今日，「同志」是這些地區的性少數人士用於自稱和互相指代的主流稱謂之一<ref name=VandeWerff>{{cite book | chapterurl = https://www.researchgate.net/publication/280095209_The_Struggle_of_the_Tongzhi_Homosexuality_in_China_and_the_Position_of_Chinese_%27Comrades%27 | chapter = The Struggle of the Tongzhi: Homosexuality in China and the Position of Chinese ‘Comrades’ | title = Urgency Required: gay and lesbian rights are human rights | page = 172-180 | publisher = HIVOS | year = 2008 | language = en | isbn = 978-9070435059 | editor1-first = Ireen | editor1-last = Dubel | editor2-first = André | editor2-last = Hielkema | first = Ties | last = Van de Werff | access-date = 2018-05-04 | archive-date = 2019-05-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190518062837/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/280095209_The_Struggle_of_the_Tongzhi_Homosexuality_in_China_and_the_Position_of_Chinese_'Comrades' | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name=qz>{{cite web | url = https://qz.com/836545/chinas-communist-party-wants-to-bring-back-the-word-comrade-but-chinas-gay-men-beat-them-to-it/ | title = “Comrade!” how gay Chinese appropriated the word the Communist Party is trying to revive | work = Quartz | first = Marta | last = Cooper | date = 2016-11-17 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = en | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20171120081308/https://qz.com/836545/chinas-communist-party-wants-to-bring-back-the-word-comrade-but-chinas-gay-men-beat-them-to-it/ | archivedate = 2017-11-20 }}</ref>。相較於「同性戀」等稱謂，「同志」被認為是更為正向、性別中立和去性化的詞彙，因而獲得很多性少數人士的青睞<ref name=qz/><ref name=nytimes/><ref name=Leung/>。它也被用來彰顯LGBT群體內的團結、情誼和包容<ref name=VandeWerff/><ref name=nytimes/>。

== 起源與使用 ==
「同志」一詞指代同性戀的含義起源於同性戀者圈子內，香港影評人[[迈克_(作家)|林邁克]]是第一個這樣使用該詞的人。他解釋稱，這一用法是以「同」字代表「同性戀」，並取「同志」一詞原有的「共同志向」之義。<ref name=nfzm>{{cite web | url = http://www.infzm.com/content/542 | title = ［电影］是是非非同性恋影展 | author = 甄晓菲 | work = 南方週末 | date = 2007-12-18 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-cn | archive-date = 2015-04-26 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150426103152/http://www.infzm.com/content/542 | dead-url = no }}</ref>

這個稱謂的興起是緣於香港劇作家[[林奕華_(香港)|林奕華]]。1989年，林奕華在香港創辦了一個以同性戀為主題的-{zh-tw:影展;zh-hk:影展;zh-cn:电影节}-，並將其中文名定為「[[香港同志影展|香港同志影展]]」（電影節的英文名為「{{lang|en|Hong Kong Lesbian and Gay Film Festival}}」，直譯為「香港[[女同性戀|女同性戀]]和[[男同性戀|男同性戀]]電影節」），取「革命尚未成功，同志仍須努力」的含義<ref name=nytimes/><ref name=nfzm/>；1992年，他在參與台灣[[金馬國際影展|金馬國際影展]]時，又將「{{lang|en|New Queer Cinema}}」譯為「{{link-en|新同志電影|New Queer Cinema}}」<ref name=Leung>{{cite book | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=_gOlgo9gvxIC&pg=PA3&lpg=PA3&dq=comrade+edward+lam&source=bl&ots=hgy3Up-uzu&sig=-0PHh8VzMoiPr1loddewFxoaIxA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj54-SPquvaAhXmxlkKHYMpCkoQ6AEIUDAG#v=onepage&q=comrade%20edward%20lam&f=false | title = Undercurrents: Queer Culture and Postcolonial Hong Kong | date = 2009-01-21 | publisher = UBC Press | page = 3 | first = Helen Hok-Sze | last = Leung | language = en | isbn = 978-0774814706 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180504080134/https://books.google.com/books?id=_gOlgo9gvxIC&pg=PA3&lpg=PA3&dq=comrade+edward+lam&source=bl&ots=hgy3Up-uzu&sig=-0PHh8VzMoiPr1loddewFxoaIxA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj54-SPquvaAhXmxlkKHYMpCkoQ6AEIUDAG#v=onepage&q=comrade%20edward%20lam&f=false | archivedate = 2018-05-04 | access-date = 2018-05-04 }}</ref><ref name=fountain>{{cite web | url = https://www.fountain.org.tw/r/post/taiwan-lgbt-movie | title = 彩虹光影的折射：小談近30年台灣同志影視 | author = 陳韋臻 | work = 新活水 | date = 2017-10-28 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-tw | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190514210234/https://www.fountain.org.tw/r/post/taiwan-lgbt-movie | archive-date = 2019-05-14 | dead-url = yes }}</ref><ref name=Ji>{{cite journal | url = https://tailit.nccu.edu.tw/download.php?filename=213_4bebb702.pdf&dir=publish&title=%25E5%2585%25A8%25E6%2596%2587%25E4%25B8%258B%25E8%25BC%2589 | title = 翻譯的公共：愛滋，同志，酷兒 | author = 紀大偉 | journal = 台灣文學學報  | page = 75-112 | date = 2015-06-30 | volume = 26 | language = zh-tw | access-date = 2018-05-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180504081950/https://tailit.nccu.edu.tw/download.php?filename=213_4bebb702.pdf&dir=publish&title=%25E5%2585%25A8%25E6%2596%2587%25E4%25B8%258B%25E8%25BC%2589 | archive-date = 2018-05-04 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>。「同志」的用法因而在香港和台灣先後流行開來，並最終流傳到中國大陸<ref name=FT/>。

[[中華民國教育部|中華民國教育部]]《[[重編國語辭典修訂本|重編國語辭典修訂本]]》中收錄了「同志」指代LGBT人群的詞義<ref name=ROCdict>{{cite web | url = http://dict.revised.moe.edu.tw/cgi-bin/cbdic/gsweb.cgi?o=dcbdic&searchid=Z00000055690 | title = 同志 - 教育部重編國語辭典修訂本 | work = 中華民國教育部 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-tw | quote = 【同志】釋義③：泛稱非異性戀者，包括同性戀、雙性戀、跨性別等，多指同性戀者而言。 | archive-date = 2021-02-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214223/http://dict.revised.moe.edu.tw/cgi-bin/cbdic/gsweb.cgi?o=dcbdic&searchid=Z00000055690 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。台灣和香港的政府都曾在官方場合下使用「同志」指代LGBT人群<ref name=brochure>{{cite web | url = https://health.gov.taipei/Portals/0/醫護管理處/心理衛生股/LGBT同志友善醫療手冊.pdf | title = LGBT同志友善醫療手冊 | work = 臺北市政府衛生局 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-tw | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160109174437/http://health.gov.taipei/Portals/0/%E9%86%AB%E8%AD%B7%E7%AE%A1%E7%90%86%E8%99%95/%E5%BF%83%E7%90%86%E8%A1%9B%E7%94%9F%E8%82%A1/LGBT%E5%90%8C%E5%BF%97%E5%8F%8B%E5%96%84%E9%86%AB%E7%99%82%E6%89%8B%E5%86%8A.pdf | archivedate = 2016-01-09 }}</ref><ref name=hkhealth>{{cite web | url = https://www.aids.gov.hk/chinese/hotline/21171069.htm | title = 愛滋病網上辦公室 -  男同志測試愛滋熱線 | work = 香港特別行政區政府衛生署 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-hk | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180504225424/https://www.aids.gov.hk/chinese/hotline/21171069.htm | archive-date = 2018-05-04 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>。一些中國大陸的民間組織和機構也以「同志」冠名<ref name=hk01/>。英文傳媒在提及「同志」一詞時通常按[[漢語拼音|漢語拼音]]將其[[轉寫|轉寫]]為「{{lang|en|tongzhi}}」<ref name=nytimes/>。

== 對原有含義的影響 ==
在近現代用法中，「同志」原指「[[同志_(政治)|革命同志]]」，被革命黨黨員在互相稱呼時使用<ref name=FT>{{cite web | url = https://www.ft.com/content/a07a5e56-aa2f-11e6-809d-c9f98a0cf216 | title = China revives ‘comrade’ in drive for Communist party discipline | work = Financial Times | first = Lucy | last = Hornby | date = 2016-11-14 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = en | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180228161741/https://www.ft.com/content/a07a5e56-aa2f-11e6-809d-c9f98a0cf216 | archivedate = 2018-02-28 }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。在台灣，這一本來含義一直以來都只在政治場合使用，時至今日也常見政黨黨員以此互稱<ref name=appledaily>{{cite web | url = http://www.chinatimes.com/newspapers/20161028000926-260306 | title = 台灣人看大陸－台灣人被稱為「同志」 | author = 路向南 | work = 旺報  | date = 2016-10-28 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-tw | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170424074657/http://www.chinatimes.com/newspapers/20161028000926-260306 | archivedate = 2017-04-24 }}</ref><ref name=oncc>{{cite web | url = http://hk.on.cc/cn/bkn/cnt/commentary/20161125/bkncn-20161125000455333-1125_05411_001.html | title = 「同志」相稱反市場 | author = 楊彼得 | work = 東網 | date = 2016-11-25 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-hk | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170704200011/http://hk.on.cc/cn/bkn/cnt/commentary/20161125/bkncn-20161125000455333-1125_05411_001.html | archivedate = 2017-07-04 }}</ref>。而在中國大陸，自[[中國共產黨|中國共產黨]]建政後，這個革命詞語一度成為全體國民使用的通用稱呼<ref name=nytimes>{{cite web | url = https://cn.nytimes.com/china/20161116/china-comrade-tongzhi-gay/en-us/ | title = China Wants to Resurrect Word ‘Comrade.’ But Its Meaning Has Changed | work = The New York Times | first = Amy | last = Qin | date = 2016-11-16 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = en | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20171123041153/https://cn.nytimes.com/china/20161116/china-comrade-tongzhi-gay/en-us/ | archivedate = 2017-11-23 }}</ref><ref name=FT/>。「同志」作為同性戀稱謂的用法在20世紀90年代開始興起時，正值其原本用法在中國大陸漸趨衰落，「同志」逐漸成為了中共黨內較高級別黨員的專用稱呼，也被用作對[[黨和國家領導人|黨和國家領導人]]的官方稱呼<ref name=nytimes/><ref name=FT/><ref name=BBCcn/>。隨著該詞的同性戀含義開始為人所知，很多人不再將「同志」用作日常生活中的通用稱謂，以避免由於歧義而引發誤解和尷尬<ref name=nytimes/><ref name=people>{{cite web | url = http://www.people.com.cn/BIG5/guandian/27/20010704/503355.html | title = 稱謂的尷尬 | author = 高為 | work = 人民日報海外版 | date = 2001-07-04 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-hant | archive-date = 2018-05-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180504092824/http://www.people.com.cn/BIG5/guandian/27/20010704/503355.html | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name=chinadaily>{{cite web | url = http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/hqgj/jryw/2013-10-22/content_10389026.html | title = 盘点那些尴尬称呼：“同志、师傅、大姐”惹忌讳 | author = 姬娜 | work = 三秦都市報 | date = 2013-10-22 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-cn | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180504080135/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/hqgj/jryw/2013-10-22/content_10389026.html | archivedate = 2018-05-04 }}</ref>。2010年，北京公交集團發布的司乘人員「文明用語規範」中，「同志」一詞僅在用於稱呼年長乘客時保留，不再對年輕乘客使用<ref name=BJMorning>{{cite web | url = http://www.chinanews.com/sh/news/2010/06-01/2314941.shtml | title = 北京公交推"文明用语" "同志"一词仅限年长乘客 | author = 陈琳 | work = 北京晨報  | date = 2010-06-01 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-cn | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180504080135/http://www.chinanews.com/sh/news/2010/06-01/2314941.shtml | archivedate = 2018-05-04 }}</ref><ref name=reuters>{{cite web | url = https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-comrade-idustre64u0wp20100531 | title = No more "comrades" on Beijing buses | work = Reuters | date = 2010-05-31 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = en | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20171114021655/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-comrade-idUSTRE64U0WP20100531 | archivedate = 2017-11-14 }}</ref>。中國大陸的年輕人對「同志」的新生用法相對而言更為熟悉，而部分年紀較長的人士則並不清楚該詞的這一含義<ref name=nytimes/><ref name=qz/>。

2012年新修訂的《[[現代漢語詞典|現代漢語詞典]]》第六版雖然收入了大量[[網路詞彙|網路詞彙]]，「同志」的詞條卻沒有收錄該詞指代LGBT群體的含義。參與詞典修訂的語言學家[[江藍生|江藍生]]稱，之所以沒有將該含義收入詞典，是因為編委會「不想提倡這些東西，不想聚焦這些東西」。<ref name=takungpao>{{cite web | url = http://paper.takungpao.com/html/2012-07/16/content_20_5.htm | title = 新漢語詞典增收社會熱詞 | work = 大公報 | date = 2012-07-16 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-hk | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180504080134/http://paper.takungpao.com/html/2012-07/16/content_20_5.htm | archivedate = 2018-05-04 }}</ref>這引發了中國大陸一些人權活動者的批評<ref name=BBC>{{cite web | url = http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-18920096 | title = New Chinese dictionary in row over 'gay' omission | work = BBC | first = Viv | last = Marsh | date = 2012-07-21 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = en | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20161129053249/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-18920096 | archivedate = 2016-11-29 }}</ref>。[[香港科技大學|香港科技大學]]社會學教授[[丁學良|丁學良]]認為，詞典編委會的這一決定說明中國官方不願意為這個重要的黨內政治稱謂添加與同性戀有關的含義<ref name=BBCcn>{{cite web | url = http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/chinese_news/2012/07/120718_china_new_dictionary | title = 《现代汉语词典》拒收“同志”引发热议 | work = BBC中文網 | date = 2012-07-18 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-hant | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180504080134/http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/chinese_news/2012/07/120718_china_new_dictionary | archivedate = 2018-05-04 }}</ref>。

2016年，[[中國共產黨第十八屆中央委員會|中國共產黨第十八屆中央委員會]]第六次全體會議通過了《關於新形勢下黨內政治生活的若干準則》，强调上下级平等、要求黨員之間一律互稱「同志」<ref name=CCPdirective>{{cite web | url = http://www.xinhuanet.com/politics/2016-11/02/c_1119838382.htm | title = 关于新形势下党内政治生活的若干准则（全文） | work = 新華社 | date = 2016-11-02 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-cn | archive-date = 2020-12-17 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201217122139/http://www.xinhuanet.com/politics/2016-11/02/c_1119838382.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>。一些同性戀者和評論人士對這一決定提出了質疑和嘲諷，認為隨著「同志」一詞本義的式微與新含義的流行，這樣的改變與時代背景格格不入<ref name=FT/><ref name=hk01>{{cite web | url = https://www.hk01.com/中國/55936/中共幹部-請叫我-同志-從一個稱謂看中國社會演變 | title = 中共幹部：請叫我「同志」！從一個稱謂看中國社會演變 | work = 香港01  | date = 2016-11-23 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = zh-hk | archive-date = 2019-05-15 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190515025338/https://www.hk01.com/%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B/55936/%E4%B8%AD%E5%85%B1%E5%B9%B9%E9%83%A8-%E8%AB%8B%E5%8F%AB%E6%88%91-%E5%90%8C%E5%BF%97-%E5%BE%9E%E4%B8%80%E5%80%8B%E7%A8%B1%E8%AC%82%E7%9C%8B%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B%E7%A4%BE%E6%9C%83%E6%BC%94%E8%AE%8A | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name=economist>{{cite web | url = https://www.economist.com/news/china/21710299-term-has-taken-new-meaning-chinas-communists-say-call-us-comrades | title = China’s Communists say call us comrades | work = The Economist | date = 2016-11-17 | accessdate = 2018-05-04 | language = en | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170211092306/http://www.economist.com/news/china/21710299-term-has-taken-new-meaning-chinas-communists-say-call-us-comrades | archivedate = 2017-02-11 }}</ref>。

